2026-05-01 RAG text sanitize for NUL and control characters

Files changed:
- backend/text_sanitizer.py
- backend/document_loader.py
- backend/parent_chunk_store.py
- backend/milvus_writer.py

Summary:
- Added a shared sanitize_text() helper.
- Removed NUL (\x00) characters.
- Removed unsafe control characters in the ranges U+0000-U+001F and U+007F-U+009F.
- Preserved newline, carriage return, and tab.
- Applied sanitization:
  - after document parsing and before chunk splitting
  - after each split level generates chunk text
  - before writing parent chunks into PostgreSQL/Redis
  - before generating embeddings and inserting documents into Milvus

Verification:
- python -m py_compile backend/text_sanitizer.py backend/document_loader.py backend/parent_chunk_store.py backend/milvus_writer.py
- Smoke test with a txt file containing NUL and other control characters
